        <p>Sharing quality data across government while delivering high impact priorities at pace is a significant challenge. Often data in these scenarios is shared through spreadsheets, documents and emails, posing substantial difficulties when collaborating with others, or when trying to leverage the latest data tools and technologies.</p>
        <p class="mt-4">Created and pioneered by Number 10's Data Science team, <a class="link" href="https://rapid.readthedocs.io/en/latest/">rAPId</a> is a standardised lightweight data sharing solution to these challenges, provided free of charge. Its aim is to enable government departments and others to securely share data in an automated way at scale, replacing the use of spreadsheets and emails to share data.</p>
        <p class="mt-4">rAPId helps match the rising demand for good-quality evidence in the design, delivery, and evaluation of public policy by providing decision and policy makers with high quality data on demand. The solution makes data more accessible for policy and decision makers and enables data professionals to work with big data shared in rAPId.</p>
